## How to verify the bundle wasn't tampered with in transit

Compute the SHA256 of what you received:

```bash
# macOS / Linux
shasum -a 256 {{bundle_filename}}
```

```powershell
# Windows
Get-FileHash {{bundle_filename}} -Algorithm SHA256
```

Compare against the SHA256 sent out-of-band (separate email, Signal message, video call):

```
{{bundle_sha256}}
```

If the hashes match, the file is byte-for-byte identical to what was packaged. If they differ, **do not trust the file** — contact the publisher.

